Subject: RE: [T2] Cooling Tin Grommets & Alt. Elbow

I've been able to use vacuum or fuel hose in place of the original cooling
tin grommets. Cut it to match the circumference of the hole, then split it
lengthwise with a razor knife. Seems to do the trick.

I bought a new alternator boot last year (bus depot?), but saw a thread a
few months later that seemed to indicate NLA. I'd guess the 914 one would
work, but don't know for sure.

Rick
'77 Westy "Pumpkin II"
